  <!-- Smallest Decanter Section -->
  <h2 id="smallest-decanter">Smallest Decanter Centrifuge</h2>

  <p>The smallest <a href="/decanter-centrifuge/">decanter centrifuge</a> is the Sharples P-660, which has a bowl diameter of approximately 6" and a bowl RPM of 6,000. The operating g-force is 3,070 Gs at full speed. The P-660 has a cyclo gearbox and uses a 7.5 HP motor.</p>

  <p>The Sharples P-660 decanter is an ideal lab-scale centrifuge to test the application of larger decanters on a smaller scale. The Sharples company originally manufactured this decanter, which Alfa Laval later took over.</p>

